<p>
	Rosewood essential oil or &#39;bois de rose&#39; as it is also known is a tropical tree growing wild in the Amazon basin. It has a sweet-woody, floral-nutmeg aroma that finds extensive use in fantasy-type perfumes and colognes.</p>
<p>
	Used in an oil burner, a few drops in the bath or blended as a massage oil or cream, rosewood oil can help with colds, coughs, fevers, infections, headaches, nervous tension, nausea and stress-related problems whilst also lifting depression and helping to counter any sexual problems including impotency.</p>
<p>
	Rosewood can also stimulate skin cells and help regenerate tissue, rejuvenating the skin which makes it particularly attractive for use with more mature complexions and/or wrinkles. The therapeutic properties of rosewood oil include anti-depressant, mildly antiseptic, aphrodisiac, bactericidal, deodorant, insecticide and stimulant.</p>
